ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
R = Right; L = Left; B = Both; 999= No Answer; 888= Skipped; 777= Condition Skipped; 555= Missing

ElementDescription: Identifies the distance from the participant's hand with which a simultaneous LED and vibration occur and identifies either a looming, receding, or baseline condition.
Notes:
The trial number corresponds to the distance and time after the beginning of the trial with which the congruent vibration and LED stimulus occur
 21 = looming 105 cm, 250 ms
 22 = looming 95 cm, 500 ms
 23 = looming 85 cm, 750 ms
 24 = looming 75 cm, 1000 ms
 25 = looming 65 cm, 1250 ms
 26 = looming 55 cm, 1500 ms
 27 = looming 45 cm, 1750 ms
 28 = looming 35 cm, 2000 ms
 29 = looming 25 cm, 2250 ms
 210 = looming 15 cm, 2500 ms
 211 = looming 5 cm, 2750 ms
 11 = receding 5 cm, 2750 ms
 12 = receding 15 cm, 2500 ms
 13 = receding 25 cm, 2250 ms
 14 = receding 35 cm, 2000 ms
 15 = receding 45 cm, 1750 ms
 16 = receding 55 cm, 1500 ms
 17 = receding 65 cm, 1250 ms
 18 = receding 75 cm, 1000 ms
 19 = receding 85 cm, 750 ms
 110 = receding 95 cm, 500 ms
 111 = receding 105 cm 250 ms
 311 = tactile only, no LEDs, 250 ms
 31 = tactile only, no LEDs, 2750 ms
 400 = visual only (looming, no vibration
 500 = visual only (receding), no vibration
